title: Photostat, "Elevations, Principal and Rear Façades, Castel d'Orgeval, Parc Beausejour, near Paris", 1904
signed: Signed on lower right of left design and center of right design in black ink: PARIS LE  SEPTEMBER 1904/ ARCHITECTE/ Hector Guimard
inscribed:
On top left in black ink: LE CASTEL D'ORGEVAL AU PARC BEAUSEJOUR/ NO.6/ PROPRIETE DE MR LAURENT/ FACADE PRINCIPALE 

On top right in black ink: LE CASTEL D'ORGEVAL AU PARC BEAUSEJOUR/ NO.8/ PROPRIETE DE MR LAURENT/ FACADE POSTERIEURE
description: Elevation plans for the Castel d'Orgeval, Parc Beausejour. The design on the left depicts the front of the building, and the right depicts the rear. Scale is noted throughout both drawings.

tombstone.epitaph:
Photostat, "Elevations, Principal and Rear Façades, Castel d'Orgeval, Parc Beausejour, near Paris", 1904.
1904. Print on off-white wove paper. Gift of Mme. Hector Guimard. 1950-66-6.
